Gemini said*Flexi Shift*




We are excited to announce the release of *Flexi Shifts*, a brand-new shift
management model designed to bring on-demand flexibility to our workforce.


Previously, shifts were entirely pre-assigned by administrators to specific
riders. With Flexi Shifts, admins can now broadcast, open and unassigned
shift slots, allowing eligible riders to view and opt-in to work based on
their own real-time availability.


Why We Built This?

Our traditional, pre-allocation system created significant operational
bottlenecks for both operations managers and the delivery fleet:

   -

   *Flexibility:* Fixed schedules restricted riders who needed dynamic
   working hours based on their daily personal schedules and earning target=
s.


   -

   *High Manual Effort:* Fleet admins spent excessive time manually
   assigning shifts and tracking down available riders, especially across
   complex captive and shared rider networks.


   -

   *Slow Supply Activation:* When sudden, unexpected order volume or
   intra-day demand spikes occurred, there was no efficient mechanism to
   quickly broadcast availability and rally willing riders.


What=E2=80=99s New!






We have completely upgraded shift management on the platform. With this
feature, we are bringing on-demand flexibility to your operational roster.

On the Rider App

   -

   *Roster & Shifts:* The *Roster* tab has been renamed to *Roster & Shifts=
*.
   Inside, riders can tap *Book Now* to claim open slots matching their
   personal schedules up to 4 days in advance.


   -

   *Smart Urgency Tags:* To accelerate shift fulfillment, riders will see
   real-time status indicators like *"Filling Fast"* or *"Almost Full"*


   -

   *Clarity on Order Properties:* Before booking, riders get full
   transparency on shift expectations, including order movement types (
   *Forward/Reverse*), payment limitations (*Prepaid/COD*), and nearby hub
   distances.


   -

   *Frictionless Cancelation:* Riders can easily cancel an accepted flexi
   shift right from their app drawer up until the moment they log in,
   instantly returning the slot back to the active supply pool.


What This Means To You






Flexi Shifts directly bridges the gap between unpredictable demand patterns
and an increasingly agile blue-collar gig workforce.

   -

   *For Admins :* Instead of calling or messaging individual riders, admins
   can scale operations instantly by broadcasting the need to an entire
   eligible rider base simultaneously.


   -

   *For Riders :* It empowers riders with full autonomy over their earning
   opportunities. They gain friction-free access to open slots on the Rider
   (executive) App without relying on manual admin intervention, allowing t=
hem
   to maximize their earnings precisely when they are willing and able to w=
ork.



What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
